{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8b137f8-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s155"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"155"},"text":"§ 155.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Fee agreements in cases under title 11 and receiverships","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Whoever, being a party in interest, whether as a debtor, creditor, receiver, trustee or representative of any of them, or attorney for any such party in interest, in any receivership or case under title 11 in any United States court or under its supervision, knowingly and fraudulently enters into any agreement, express or implied, with another such party in interest or attorney for another such party in interest, for the purpose of fixing the fees or other compensation to be paid to any party in interest or to any attorney for any party in interest for services rendered in connection therewith, from the assets of the estate, shall be fined under this title or imprisoned not more than one year, or both.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8b137f9-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 645","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/690"},"text":"62 Stat. 690","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-05-24/ch139/s4"},"text":"May 24, 1949, ch. 139, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/90"},"text":"63 Stat. 90","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/tIII/s314/f/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598, title III, § 314(f)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2677"},"text":"92 Stat. 2677","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322/tXXXIII/s330016/1/K"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322, title XXXIII, § 330016(1)(K)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2147"},"text":"108 Stat. 2147","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8b137fa-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb8b137fb-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb8b137fc-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"1948 ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s572a"},"text":"section 572a of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., Judicial Code and Judiciary ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1937-08-25/ch777"},"text":"Aug. 25, 1937, ch. 777","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/50/810"},"text":"50 Stat. 810","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “upon conviction” were deleted as surplusage since punishment can be imposed only after a conviction.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A fine of “$5,000” was substituted for “$10,000” and “one year” for “five years”, to reduce the offense to the grade of a misdemeanor and the punishment to an amount and term proportionate to the gravity of the offense.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Minor changes were made in phraseology.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb8b137fd-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"1949 ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This amendment [see section 4] clarifies ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s155"},"text":"section 155 of title 18","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., by restating the first paragraph thereof in closer conformity with the original law, as it existed at the time of the enactment of the revision of title 18."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8b137fe-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb8b137ff-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322","children":[],"tail":" substituted “fined under this title” for “fined not more than $5,000”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" substituted “cases under title 11 and receiverships” for “bankruptcy proceedings” in section catchline and in text “or case under title 11” for “, bankruptcy or reorganization proceeding”, inserted “knowingly and fraudulently” after “supervision,”, and struck out penalty provision for a judge of a United States court to knowingly approve the payment of any fees or compensation that were fixed."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1949—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1949","children":[],"tail":", inserted references to attorneys for any party in interest in three places, and substituted “in any United States court or under its supervision” for “in or under the supervision of any court of the United States”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb8b13800-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idb8b13801-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1978 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/s402/a"},"text":"section 402(a) of Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 11","children":[],"tail":", Bankruptcy."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"savings","id":"idb8b13802-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Savings Provision","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/s314"},"text":"section 314 of Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" not to affect the application of chapter 9 (§ 151 et seq.), chapter 96 (§ 1961 et seq.), or section 2516, 3057, or 3284 of this title to any act of any person (1) committed before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", or (2) committed after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", in connection with a case commenced before such date, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/s403/d"},"text":"section 403(d) of Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 11","children":[],"tail":", Bankruptcy."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
